<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  shotAI distribution entitlements.

  Deliberately EMPTY:
  - NOT App-Sandboxed. shotAI needs CGEventTap + Accessibility (AX) + a Carbon
    hotkey, all of which the sandbox forbids. Sandbox is only required for the Mac
    App Store, which this app can't target anyway — Developer ID distribution is
    unsandboxed and fine.
  - NO hardened-runtime exception entitlements are needed. Screen Recording
    (ScreenCaptureKit), Accessibility, and Input Monitoring (the event tap) are
    all TCC-gated at RUNTIME, not blocked by the hardened runtime. The app loads
    no third-party/unsigned dylibs, uses no JIT and no DYLD overrides, so none of
    the com.apple.security.cs.* exceptions apply.
  - MUST NOT contain com.apple.security.get-task-allow — notarization rejects it.
    (Release builds don't add it; signing with this empty file guarantees its
    absence.)

  If a future need arises (e.g. loading an unsigned plug-in), add the specific
  com.apple.security.cs.* key here rather than weakening the whole runtime.
-->
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict/>
</plist>
